wikipedia_page.main: Vane Hungerford Pennell (16 August 1876 – 17 June 1938) was an English rackets and real tennis player who competed in the 1908 Summer Olympics for Great Britain.

link_mentions.page: John Jacob Astor, 1st Baron Astor of Hever
response: Astor represented Great Britain in rackets at the 1908 Summer Olympics, winning the gold medal in the men's doubles competition together with Vane Pennell, and winning bronze in the men's singles event.
